<h2>The Challenge</h2>

<div class="side-by-side">
  <p class="big">
    {{ subtitle }}
  </p>
  <p>
    In collaboration with Xbox Game Pass and Verizon, I helped bring massive Sea
    of Thieves and Minecraft events to life through a series of high-profile
    gaming events, cinematic trailers, and custom tournament branding, all
    designed to inform and attract fans to Verizon's All-Access Campaign with
    Xbox. These promotional events combined engaging storytelling, immersive
    in-game visuals, and creator-led broadcasts to make All-Access a visible
    force in the gaming space. I had to keep in mind:
  </p>
</div>

<div class="side-by-side">
  <p>
    1. Unlike traditional esports titles, Sea of Thieves and Minecraft don’t
    have built-in competitive formats. Each event needed to be custom-designed
    to create thrilling gameplay moments while keeping Verizon’s brand
    integration organic and immersive.
  </p>
  <p>
    2. The success of these campaigns would depend on drawing high-profile
    gaming creators to drive engagement, meaning the content strategy needed to
    capture attention before, during, and after the events.
  </p>
  <p>
    3. From Verizon-branded hub worlds in Minecraft to dynamic tournament
    branding in Sea of Thieves, the challenge was ensuring the branding felt
    natural while reinforcing Xbox’s All Access messaging.
  </p>
</div>

