    <p>
      For the Holiday Clash tournament, we took the Bilge Rat Bingo format and
      reworked it into a winter-themed competition, keeping the high-energy
      pacing while adding holiday-inspired challenges. The Holiday Clash
      introduced seasonal, thematic challenges as players raced to steal
      treasure, sink rival ships, and complete in-game holiday-themed
      objectives.
    </p>
    <p>
      With 1,400 average concurrent viewers and 200K social impressions, Holiday
      Clash reinforced Sea of Thieves as a community-driven competitive sandbox,
      proving the tournament format’s long-term potential.
    </p>
